law.catch_line: Qualifications of laboratory personnel may be prescribed.
law.text: The cabinet may prescribe minimal qualifications for medical laboratory personnel including but not limited to microbiology, serology, chemistry, hematology, immunohematology, biophysics, cytology, or pathology.
law.history: Amended 2015 Ky. Acts ch. 113, sec. 23, effective June 24, 2015. -- Amended 1990 Ky. Acts ch. 443, sec. 26, effective July 13, 1990. -- Created 1968 Ky. Acts ch. 180, sec. 17.
